      "content": "The problem is the board doesn't want \"context-specific adjustments.\" They want a clean break from the neural layer because the current \"context\" being used is getting us sued for racial profiling. They're saying the current pattern recognition is biased and we need a system that doesn't make assumptions about people based on demographic profiles. How do you respond to the claim that your \"nuanced\" detection is just a mask for biased profiling?",
